138
00:06:18,690 --> 00:06:22,760
Someone posted it on Tube-Tube.
Only 12 people have seen it.

139
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:26,100
12 people?!
That's half the town!

140
00:06:26,130 --> 00:06:27,670
I'm finished, Universe.

141
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,330
I don't know of many political figures

142
00:06:29,370 --> 00:06:30,470
that have made a comeback

143
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,640
after getting a tomato to the face.

144
00:06:32,670 --> 00:06:36,270
Oh, again, and again,
and again, and again.

145
00:06:36,310 --> 00:06:38,110
You need to stop looping that.

146
00:06:38,140 --> 00:06:41,350
Look, we're gonna
get through this together, okay?

147
00:06:41,380 --> 00:06:42,880
Tomorrow is the big debate.

148
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:45,950
You still have one more chance
to win back the town's love.

149
00:06:45,990 --> 00:06:48,755
But Steven, some of the
things people have been

150
00:06:48,756 --> 00:06:51,520
saying about me are
really painful and mean.

151
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,520
We've just got to change
the conversation.

152
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,130
We can start with this.

153
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:58,900
"How to talk to people"?

154
00:06:58,930 --> 00:07:01,170
I'm going to get you ready
for that debate,

155
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:05,240
even if it takes all night.

156
00:07:05,270 --> 00:07:07,370
[Crowd murmuring]

157
00:07:07,410 --> 00:07:09,370
All right.
[Yawns]

158
00:07:09,410 --> 00:07:10,680
Today's the day.

159
00:07:10,710 --> 00:07:12,210
You got your note cards,
you look great,

160
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,380
and if anyone brings up
the alien invasion thing,

161
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:16,710
I wrote a bunch of Ocean Town
jokes for you to use.

162
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:18,980
Aww, shucks, Universe.

163
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:21,420
You're like the son
I never had.

164
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:23,390
You...have a son.

165
00:07:23,420 --> 00:07:24,890
I know that.

166
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:27,690
You're just very different
from him, is all.

167
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:28,660
[Crowd chanting "speech"]

168
00:07:28,690 --> 00:07:29,860
[Whines]

169
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,600
I'm rooting for you,
Dew Drops.

170
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:33,060
[Weakly] Thanks.

171
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:35,130
[Chanting continues]

172
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,280
[Chanting stops]

173
00:07:47,310 --> 00:07:48,850
[Clears throat]
[Microphone feedback]

174
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,620
People of Beach City.

175
00:07:50,650 --> 00:07:53,050
You might think
that being a mayor is a fine

176
00:07:53,090 --> 00:07:55,090
and glamorous
sort of thing.

177
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:58,920
I can understand why my opponent
would want the position.

178
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:01,930
But I've been mayor of this city
for a decade,

179
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:05,930
and I know some things
that Ms. Nanefua does not.

180
00:08:05,970 --> 00:08:09,870
You see, when you're the mayor,
you get blamed for everything.

181
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:13,770
When the boardwalk has termites,
it's the mayor's fault.

182
00:08:13,810 --> 00:08:17,810
When aliens steal people,
it's the mayor's fault.

183
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:19,940
When the mayor crashes
the mayor mobile

184
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:25,250
into the only cell tower
in town, it's the mayor's fault.

185
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:29,150
Most people can't handle that
kind of pressure, but I can.

186
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:32,120
So, I say to you,
Beach City citizens,

187
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,660
just enjoy our wonderful ocean breeze

188
00:08:34,690 --> 00:08:36,630
and don't worry about a thing.

189
00:08:36,660 --> 00:08:40,460
Just let Dewey "do" it for you!

190
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,430
[Crowd murmuring,
applause]

191
00:08:43,470 --> 00:08:44,640
Nice.

192
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:47,440
You know, Mayor Dewey,
you are right.

193
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:49,770
I am?
A-About what?

194
00:08:49,810 --> 00:08:53,310
I have blamed you
for too many things,

195
00:08:53,350 --> 00:08:55,410
and that is not helping.

196
00:08:55,450 --> 00:08:57,320
[Crowd murmuring]

197
00:08:57,350 --> 00:08:58,580
What?

198
00:08:58,620 --> 00:09:00,990
Blaming our problems
completely on the mayor

199
00:09:01,020 --> 00:09:03,290
is not getting us
anywhere.

200
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:07,460
When one of us suffers,
the town suffers.

201
00:09:07,490 --> 00:09:12,830
When you suffer, Mayor Billiam,
the town suffers.

202
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:16,800
So, no longer will I
point my fingers at you.

203
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:21,610
I will extend all my fingers
on both my hands

204
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,840
to everyone here today

205
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:26,810
and ask that we share
responsibility

206
00:09:26,850 --> 00:09:31,720
for the welfare and safety
of Beach City, together!

207
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:33,650
Thank you.

208
00:09:33,690 --> 00:09:35,520
[Cheers and applause]

209
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:40,660
[Chanting "Nanefua"]

210
00:09:40,690 --> 00:09:42,690
You got this, Mayor Dewey.

211
00:09:42,730 --> 00:09:45,030
[Stammering]

212
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:49,870
Uh, did you ever notice
how people from Ocean Town ...

213
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:52,540
Oh, who am I kidding?

214
00:09:52,570 --> 00:09:55,040
Beach City deserves
a real mayor.

215
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:58,740
Someone wise and collected
like Ms. Nanefua.

216
00:09:58,780 --> 00:10:00,380
[Crowd murmuring]

217
00:10:00,410 --> 00:10:01,910
Wait.
No, no, no.

218
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:04,550
I withdraw
from the race.

219
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:09,020
You can find the key to the city
under the city welcome mat.

220
00:10:09,050 --> 00:10:12,320
[Cheers and applause]

221
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:14,020
[Sighs]

222
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:16,060
Mayor Dewey,
what're you doing?!

223
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:18,230
Y-You can't just
throw the election like that.

224
00:10:18,260 --> 00:10:19,860
W-We could still win!

225
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,870
Well, I know
it's not very traditional

226
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:25,370
to do that in the middle of
a debate, but why drag it out?

227
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:28,670
We could have won!
I-I really believed in you!

228
00:10:28,710 --> 00:10:32,080
- I really believed in us!
- Well, you were wrong.

229
00:10:32,110 --> 00:10:36,080
- What do you want me to say?
- How about, "I'm sorry.

230
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,680
We were in this together,
and I let you down."

231
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,120
Come on, Universe.

232
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:42,950
You know she's gonna be
a better mayor than me.

233
00:10:42,990 --> 00:10:45,060
It was the right thing to do.

234
00:10:45,090 --> 00:10:50,390
I guess, but... I still feel betrayed.

235
00:10:50,430 --> 00:10:53,260
That's probably how Connie feels.

236
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,070
Yeah, I don't know
what you're talking about,

237
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:57,270
but I've got to find a new job.

238
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:59,600
[Humming]

239
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:03,440
[Tapping, phone dialing]

240
